au.gov.ansto.bragg.process.processor
Interface Processor

All Superinterfaces:
au.gov.ansto.bragg.base.common.All, Common, au.gov.ansto.bragg.base.common.Publisher, java.io.Serializable
All Known Subinterfaces:
CompositeProcessor, Framework, Sink, Source
public interface Processor
extends Common

Generic Processor class. Processor instance will do data processing with static library methods.

A Processor instance is built from an algorithm recipe xml file. It will call a concrete processor to do a data processing. The In, Var and Out ports are built upon the processor to take and pass signals.

Processor is the ancestor class for CompositeProcessor and Framework. The processing procedure will be trigered if all the Var ports are set and all the In ports are ready for processing. After the processing, it will output the result signal to its Out ports and its Out ports are in charge of where the signal flows.

setRecipeID

void setRecipeID(int recipeID)
This method is called by In ports of this processor, when the In port is ready. When this method is called, the processor will check if all In singals are ready, by checking if the token pool is empty. If true, the processor will do processing by calling transfer().

Parameters:
recipeID - in int type
